description: Git commit authorship — never add Cursor as author or co-author
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git commits and authorship

- Commits must be authored only by the repository owner's GitHub identity.
- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor` or any `Co-authored-by: *cursor*` trailer.
- Never set the commit author or committer to Cursor / cursoragent.
- If the environment injects a Cursor co-author trailer, rewrite the commit (e.g. `git commit-tree`) so the final commit message has no Cursor trailer before pushing.
- Do not use `--trailer` flags that add Cursor attribution.
